Travelers who use the I-5/Interstate Bridge between Vancouver and Portland should prepare for an overnight full closure of the southbound span starting at 11 p.m. Saturday July 31 and continuing until 7 a.m. Sunday Aug. 1. ?Note: During the closure travelers on southbound I-5 who wish to continue into Oregon can exit I-5 using Exit 1A for SR 14 east or use I-205 south into Oregon. The sidewalk on the southbound span will close but the sidewalk on the northbound span will remain open. The Interstate Bridge is jointly owned by Oregon and Washington and is maintained by ODOT. The northbound span opened in 1917 and the southbound span in 1958. For questions about this project contact Don Hamilton at 503-704-7452
